<br>
I tend to play a lot solo but also like to make friends and am willing to help most anyone (except beggars and whiners) at any time.<br>
<br>
I enjoy roleplaying (beginning in pen and paper many years ago) but do not believe 'thee' and 'thou' are necessary to remain in character.<br>
<br>
I'm looking for a group that enjoys the game and enjoys playing the game and is not all caught up in leveling, leveling, leveling but, at the same time, active in the lands of Norrath.<br>
<br>
My 'roleplay' history for &quot;Prinus&quot;, my mage, follows:<br>
<br>
I was born in Erud on the Isle of Odus to a family of staid merchants.  My life was one of peace and prosperity.. and boredom (smile) with the exceptions of the visits from my Uncle Ravan.  Almost as much fun as listening to his tales of far off lands and adventures was the dark look in my father's eye when Uncle Ravan's figure stood at our door.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, in my late teens my uncle ceased to come for visits.  When I reached and age to take out on my own, despite my father's refusal to allow it, I used my time of researching in Erud's library and small stock of mage lore to venture into the depths of Toxula forest and test myself against it's denizens.  Later I journeyed to the lesser human city of Qeynos and continued my self testing and my education into the ways of the Mage.<br>
<br>
Today I am, while still young in magic, beginning to gain some power and seek to journey far in this land to seek word of my lost uncle and, if I find he has fallen, to make those responsible pay.  Yes, pay dearly.&quot;<br>
<br>
I play in the Easter Time Zone mostly between 5:30 PM and 10Pm weekdays, afternoons/evenings on Saturdays and Most of the day on Sundays.<br>
<br>
If you think your guild might find a place for one such as I, please respond here or give &quot;prinus&quot; a tell.<br>
